===Etymology===
From ''[[titmose]]'', from ''[[tit#Etymology 2|tit]]'', + Old English ''[[mase]]'' (titmouse). The plural is formed in imitation of the otherwise unrelated ''[[mouse]]''.  

===Noun===
{{en-noun|titmice}}

# Any small [[passerine]] bird of the family [[Paridae]], which are found in the [[woods]] of the [[northern hemisphere]] and of [[Africa]].

